of the word lynching...

820
01:03:56,816 --> 01:03:59,148
If counsel's ears were as quick
as his objections...

821
01:03:59,318 --> 01:04:01,377
...he'd know I said
attempted lynching.

822
01:04:01,621 --> 01:04:04,988
If the state's evidence was
as breathtaking as its sarcasm...

823
01:04:05,157 --> 01:04:08,820
...which I suggest is being employed
to hide from the jury...

824
01:04:08,995 --> 01:04:12,487
...the failure of its own witnesses
to back up its hollow case...

825
01:04:12,665 --> 01:04:15,566
Hooray! Hollow as a busted jug,
is what it is!

826
01:04:15,735 --> 01:04:17,396
Quiet, will you?

827
01:04:17,770 --> 01:04:19,328
Remove that man.

828
01:04:20,573 --> 01:04:22,700
- I was just...
- Come here. You're going.

829
01:04:23,776 --> 01:04:28,042
They hadn't ought to treat Uncle Billy
that way! Uncle Billy's right!

830
01:04:28,214 --> 01:04:31,274
This is a shame against the good name
of our town.

831
01:04:32,418 --> 01:04:36,445
- Bring that man before the court.
- Order in the court. Quiet.

832
01:04:36,656 --> 01:04:39,056
He won't do nothing to me.
I ain't afraid.

833
01:04:39,225 --> 01:04:40,749
Sit down, you. Sit down!

834
01:04:42,161 --> 01:04:44,891
