945
01:12:13,045 --> 01:12:17,505
He never thought of buying
things like that for himself.

946
01:12:18,650 --> 01:12:22,381
And then I stopped at
the minister's to remind him...

947
01:12:22,554 --> 01:12:26,650
<i>... that Joe and I would be there</i>
<i>at 4:00, and not to forget.</i>

948
01:12:28,227 --> 01:12:30,855
<i>We'd been away from</i>
<i>each other so long.</i>

949
01:12:31,030 --> 01:12:33,260
<i>More than a year.</i>

950
01:12:33,932 --> 01:12:37,891
<i>And l</i>... <i>I loved him so.</i>

951
01:13:08,367 --> 01:13:11,803
<i>I turn the witness over to the defense.</i>

952
01:13:12,171 --> 01:13:15,231
<i>Miss Grant. According to</i>
<i>the fact of psychology...</i>

953
01:13:15,407 --> 01:13:19,741
...that under great emotional stress
the mind sees what it has expected to...

954
01:13:19,912 --> 01:13:22,472
...whether the thing
is actually there or not...

955
01:13:22,681 --> 01:13:26,742
...is it not possible that you
did not see Joseph Wilson...

956
01:13:26,919 --> 01:13:30,821
...but only the image of him your
imagination had created in your head?

957
01:13:30,989 --> 01:13:34,584
No, I saw him. I saw him
burning to death there!

958
01:13:34,760 --> 01:13:38,389
You can see that picture now
too, can't you?

959
01:13:38,564 --> 01:13:40,998
- I'll always see it.
- So perhaps after all...

960
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:45,500
...it was an hallucination of your tortured
mind that you saw there...

961
01:13:45,704 --> 01:13:47,899
...just as you see it here.

962
01:13:48,073 --> 01:13:51,770
What do you want me to say,
yes or no? I tell you I saw him.

963
01:13:51,944 --> 01:13:56,438
Can you, from your
own personal knowledge...

964
01:13:56,615 --> 01:13:59,413
...swear that Joseph Wilson is dead?

965
01:13:59,585 --> 01:14:02,145
Why, no. That is, yes.

966
01:14:02,321 --> 01:14:04,949
- I mean, one can assume.
- Excuse me...

967
01:14:05,124 --> 01:14:09,151
...but that is exactly what must not
be assumed, but proved!

968
01:14:09,328 --> 01:14:13,162
The state is asking the lives
of 22 people for one.

969
01:14:13,332 --> 01:14:15,664
I don't care about the lives of 22 people!

970
01:14:15,834 --> 01:14:18,268
They can't bring back
the life I cared about.

971
01:14:18,437 --> 01:14:23,670
I only wish I hadn't fainted. I wish I could
have gone in there to him. With him.

972
01:14:24,143 --> 01:14:26,373
That's all, Miss Grant.

973
01:14:33,685 --> 01:14:36,950
I will remind the jury
that under the law...

974
01:14:37,122 --> 01:14:41,491
...lives must not be taken on
assumptions but on facts!

975
01:14:41,660 --> 01:14:44,220
Where is the corpse of Joseph Wilson?

976
01:14:44,396 --> 01:14:47,729
<i>The law is that the corpus</i>
<i>delicti must be established...</i>

977
01:14:47,900 --> 01:14:50,027
<i>... at least by fragments</i>
<i>of the human body...</i>

978
01:14:50,202 --> 01:14:54,639
<i>... or of articles known and proved</i>
<i>to have been worn by the deceased.</i>

979
01:14:54,973 --> 01:14:58,636
And in the absence of convincing proof
of the corpus delicti...

980
01:14:58,810 --> 01:15:01,643
...I move this indictment
be wiped off the records...

981
01:15:01,847 --> 01:15:05,339
...and the charges against
these defendants be dismissed.

982
01:15:05,517 --> 01:15:09,544
I shall take the motion for dismissal
under advisement until tomorrow...

983
01:15:10,055 --> 01:15:12,717
<i>... and hear the state's arguments then.</i>

984
01:15:27,039 --> 01:15:29,769
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

985
01:15:29,942 --> 01:15:31,876
...I have received an object...

986
01:15:32,044 --> 01:15:33,909
...which, if authentic...

987
01:15:34,079 --> 01:15:36,946
...must be considered
as evidence in this case.

988
01:15:37,316 --> 01:15:42,219
As to its authenticity, I am not
permitted to have an opinion.

989
01:15:42,387 --> 01:15:46,448
However, in order to present it to you...

990
01:15:46,625 --> 01:15:49,389
...I must take the witness stand.

991
01:15:50,562 --> 01:15:52,120
Mr. Clerk...

992
01:15:52,331 --> 01:15:54,060
...please swear me.

993
01:15:59,104 --> 01:16:02,767
Do you swear that you'll tell the truth
and nothing but the truth?

994
01:16:02,941 --> 01:16:05,136
- I do.
- Please be seated.

995
01:16:07,546 --> 01:16:10,310
This is a special delivery
letter postmarked...

996
01:16:10,482 --> 01:16:13,747
...in this city at 11 p.m. Last night...

997
01:16:13,919 --> 01:16:19,050
...and addressed "Judge Daniel Hopkins,
Hall of Justice, Courtroom 10."

998
01:16:19,424 --> 01:16:22,621
Is this the letter you received,
Your Honor?

999
01:16:27,966 --> 01:16:29,593
It is.

1000
01:16:31,136 --> 01:16:33,730
The communication is not handwritten.

1001
01:16:33,905 --> 01:16:37,068
It is formed by letters cut
from a newspaper...

1002
01:16:37,242 --> 01:16:39,972
...and pasted together to spell words.

1003
01:16:40,145 --> 01:16:43,945
It is, ladies and gentlemen, the
confession of a tortured conscience.

1004
01:16:44,116 --> 01:16:45,447
Listen.

1005
01:16:45,617 --> 01:16:47,778
"I can't hide the truth any longer.

1006
01:16:47,953 --> 01:16:52,014
I am a citizen of Strand
who helped clean up the jail mess.

1007
01:16:52,190 --> 01:16:55,785
In the ashes,
I found this enclosed ring.

1008
01:16:55,961 --> 01:17:01,297
Nobody knew it, so I was keeping it for
a mement... Memento.

1009
01:17:01,466 --> 01:17:03,696
But it is upsetting my conscience.

1010
01:17:03,902 --> 01:17:08,134
I don't dare sign this, or I would
probably get lynched myself.

1011
01:17:08,307 --> 01:17:11,037
A citizen of Strand."

1012
01:17:15,180 --> 01:17:17,444
I now draw your attention to this ring.

1013
01:17:17,616 --> 01:17:21,780
It's gold, melted and misshapen,
as if by fire.

1014
01:17:21,987 --> 01:17:26,651
Inside the ring is an engraved
inscription, reading...

1015
01:17:26,858 --> 01:17:29,053
I can decipher only the words...

1016
01:17:29,227 --> 01:17:32,219
..."Henry to K."

1017
01:17:32,431 --> 01:17:34,023
The rest is melted out.

1018
01:17:34,700 --> 01:17:37,931
But after that word, I can plainly read...

1019
01:17:38,136 --> 01:17:40,468
...in a different style of engraving...

1020
01:17:40,639 --> 01:17:43,005
..."To Joe," obviously meaning...

1021
01:17:43,175 --> 01:17:45,234
- Objection!
- Sustained.

1022
01:17:45,444 --> 01:17:48,709
Since when have anonymous letters
become gospel in law?

1023
01:17:48,880 --> 01:17:52,179
Who can say that ring was
the property of Joseph Wilson?

1024
01:17:52,351 --> 01:17:54,546
What proof is there that it was found...

1025
01:17:54,720 --> 01:17:57,985
...as that concocted letter
would have us believe?

1026
01:17:58,156 --> 01:18:01,523
Who sent that letter?
A man afraid to sign his name.

1027
01:18:02,027 --> 01:18:05,258
I believe that this fraud is
a fabrication of some soul...

1028
01:18:06,965 --> 01:18:09,957
...poisoned with hostility
toward these defendants!

1029
01:18:10,268 --> 01:18:14,204
The state recalls
Katherine Grant to the stand.

1030
01:18:24,716 --> 01:18:29,244
I will remind you, Miss Grant,
you've already sworn to tell the truth.

1031
01:18:30,589 --> 01:18:33,752
Have you ever seen this ring before?

1032
01:18:35,794 --> 01:18:39,025
- Yes.
- Where and when?

1033
01:18:39,698 --> 01:18:42,394
In the railroad station in Chicago.

1034
01:18:42,567 --> 01:18:44,762
When I was leaving to come here.

1035
01:18:44,936 --> 01:18:46,699
I gave it to Joe.

1036
01:18:46,872 --> 01:18:50,399
What did Joseph Wilson do with it
when you gave it to him?

1037
01:18:51,410 --> 01:18:53,810
He put it on his little finger.

1038
01:18:54,012 --> 01:18:56,708
It was too small for any other finger.

1039
01:18:56,882 --> 01:19:00,079
How can you be sure this ring
is the one you gave him...

1040
01:19:00,252 --> 01:19:03,449
...and saw him put
on his little finger there?

1041
01:19:06,024 --> 01:19:08,322
Because it was my mother's.

1042
01:19:08,927 --> 01:19:13,796
It had engraved "Henry,"
my father's name...

1043
01:19:14,466 --> 01:19:18,232
..."to Katherine," which was
my mother's name too.

1044
01:19:19,938 --> 01:19:22,429
After the "Katherine"...

1045
01:19:22,841 --> 01:19:25,309
...I had it engraved...

1046
01:19:26,077 --> 01:19:28,170
..."to Joe."

1047
01:19:30,315 --> 01:19:32,078
I want to confess!

1048
01:19:32,250 --> 01:19:33,740
Let me go!

1049
01:19:33,919 --> 01:19:35,477
I threw stones at him!

1050
01:19:35,687 --> 01:19:37,018
I helped kill him!

1051
01:19:37,189 --> 01:19:40,283
I'm guilty! We're all guilty!

1052
01:19:40,459 --> 01:19:44,862
Let me ask her to forgive me!
Please, please, forgive me!

1053
01:19:45,096 --> 01:19:46,620
Forgive me!

1054
01:19:46,798 --> 01:19:48,857
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1055
01:19:49,067 --> 01:19:50,762
Forgive me!

1056
01:19:50,936 --> 01:19:53,769
...there is your answer to this case!

1057
01:19:55,807 --> 01:19:58,799
That letter cinched it for us, didn't it?

1058
01:19:59,778 --> 01:20:01,803
Yeah, why?

1059
01:20:02,080 --> 01:20:05,174
It was certainly lucky for us
that it showed up...

1060
01:20:05,350 --> 01:20:08,114
...wasn't it?
- Stop talking about it.

1061
01:20:08,286 --> 01:20:09,844
I mean...

1062
01:20:10,021 --> 01:20:12,387
...where does it get you?

1063
01:20:15,627 --> 01:20:18,494
- Why didn't you tell me Joe was alive?
- What?

1064
01:20:18,663 --> 01:20:21,496
- Are you crazy?
- I know he's alive, Charlie. I know.

1065
01:20:21,666 --> 01:20:23,691
Will you shut your mouth?

1066
01:20:24,236 --> 01:20:26,864
You can't keep me quiet.
What's happened to him?

1067
01:20:27,038 --> 01:20:30,303
Does he realize what he's done?
What we've all done?

1068
01:20:30,475 --> 01:20:32,340
- Where is he?
- You saw him.

1069
01:20:32,511 --> 01:20:34,502
You saw him in that fire.
Why ask me?

1070
01:20:34,679 --> 01:20:37,648
You testified, not me. I wasn't there.

1071
01:20:37,816 --> 01:20:40,512
You're losing your mind again.

1072
01:20:42,320 --> 01:20:44,311
Of course.

1073
01:20:44,689 --> 01:20:46,884
Of course you're right.

1074
01:20:49,494 --> 01:20:52,019
I don't know what's the matter with me.

1075
01:20:52,697 --> 01:20:54,528
Of course you're right.

1076
01:20:54,699 --> 01:20:56,360
He's dead.

1077
01:20:57,669 --> 01:21:00,832
But I haven't slept for so long.

1078
01:21:01,673 --> 01:21:03,664
I want to go.

1079
01:21:03,842 --> 01:21:06,402
I can't listen to any more.
I want to go home.

1080
01:21:08,380 --> 01:21:11,213
It was that letter that made her jump.
I don't know...

1081
01:21:11,383 --> 01:21:13,613
You're trying to make yourself important.

1082
01:21:13,785 --> 01:21:16,948
- Katherine suspicious? You're daffy!
- I'm daffy!

1083
01:21:17,155 --> 01:21:20,090
Take a look at your radio.
I tell you, that letter...

1084
01:21:20,258 --> 01:21:23,091
That letter was the best idea I ever had.

1085
01:21:23,261 --> 01:21:26,697
Yeah. Almost cost me my finger
getting that ring off.

1086
01:21:26,865 --> 01:21:31,165
But it was worth it. It would have been
worth the whole hand. Two hands.

1087
01:21:31,736 --> 01:21:34,933
Tom, why don't you stick with me?
You know as well...

1088
01:21:35,106 --> 01:21:38,473
Yeah, you're right.
What's the use of fighting with him?

1089
01:21:38,677 --> 01:21:42,579
Anyway, she's home now.
We got the landlady to put her to bed.

1090
01:21:43,381 --> 01:21:46,373
Must have been some sensation
when that woman collapsed.

1091
01:21:46,585 --> 01:21:48,917
They could stand seeing
me burned to death.

1092
01:21:49,087 --> 01:21:51,681
- They can't stand an honest trial.
- Cut it out!

1093
01:21:51,890 --> 01:21:54,450
I can't stand it!
I can't hear any more!

1094
01:21:54,626 --> 01:21:58,585
You haven't been watching them.
You didn't look in their eyes.

1095
01:21:58,763 --> 01:22:02,927
- Yellow-livered welsher, sorry for them.
- You're as bad! You're lynching me!

1096
01:22:03,101 --> 01:22:07,561
It's getting me too. I wish I hadn't
started the whole thing. I was with you.

1097
01:22:07,739 --> 01:22:10,401
But I got a feeling you talked
me into something.

1098
01:22:10,575 --> 01:22:12,406
If I could think of a way out...

1099
01:22:12,577 --> 01:22:14,135
Why don't you snitch on me!

1100
01:22:14,312 --> 01:22:18,442
- Nobody's talking about that!
- I am! I can't stand it any longer!

1101
01:22:19,250 --> 01:22:20,649
Be human, Joe.

1102
01:22:20,819 --> 01:22:23,083
We can get out of the country,
start over.

1103
01:22:23,254 --> 01:22:27,657
But let's tell them the truth.
Let's tell them you're alive!

1104
01:22:29,227 --> 01:22:31,593
I'll kill you first.

1105
01:22:34,132 --> 01:22:37,033
You might as well kill me too.

1106
01:22:42,107 --> 01:22:44,007
You brought her here, you lying...

1107
01:22:44,175 --> 01:22:45,642
No, Joe. I followed them!

1108
01:22:45,810 --> 01:22:50,645
I knew you were alive when I saw your
letter. Why not kill me! Do a good job!

1109
01:22:50,815 --> 01:22:54,717
What difference does it make?
Twenty-two, 23, 25!

1110
01:22:54,886 --> 01:22:57,354
- Listen to me, Joe.
- No!

1111
01:22:59,824 --> 01:23:01,553
I'm sorry.

1112
01:23:01,760 --> 01:23:04,228
I didn't mean to talk that way.

1113
01:23:04,396 --> 01:23:07,888
Joe, I understand how you feel...

1114
01:23:08,066 --> 01:23:10,534
...and I understand
why you feel that way.

1115
01:23:10,702 --> 01:23:12,670
When I thought you were dead...

1116
01:23:12,837 --> 01:23:16,068
...when I thought of what killed you,
I wanted revenge too.

1117
01:23:16,274 --> 01:23:17,832
But now I don't.

1118
01:23:18,009 --> 01:23:22,378
I want to be happy again. I want what
we've always promised each other.

1119
01:23:22,547 --> 01:23:25,516
You ought to have violins
playing when you talk.

1120
01:23:25,684 --> 01:23:29,518
- I know what I want, and I'm getting it!
- You're hanging 22 people!

1121
01:23:29,688 --> 01:23:32,987
No, I'm not. I'm hanging 22 rats
for something they did do.

1122
01:23:33,158 --> 01:23:34,989
- These are 22 human beings.
- Yeah.

1123
01:23:35,160 --> 01:23:38,323
- They live and breathe.
- Like me in the jail, for instance!

1124
01:23:38,496 --> 01:23:41,556
They're not murderers.
They were part of a mob.

1125
01:23:41,733 --> 01:23:46,067
- A mob doesn't think. It hasn't time.
- What about the guy in jail? He can think.

1126
01:23:46,237 --> 01:23:50,037
All right, it's his turn. Let them know
what it means to be lynched.

1127
01:23:50,208 --> 01:23:52,369
- Don't you think they know by now?
- No.

1128
01:23:52,544 --> 01:23:57,413
What you've felt for a few hours,
they've had to face for days and weeks!

1129
01:23:57,582 --> 01:24:02,246
Wishing, with all their souls, they could
have that one day to live over again.

1130
01:24:04,055 --> 01:24:05,579
Joe...

1131
01:24:06,524 --> 01:24:08,458
...don't you see?

1132
01:24:08,927 --> 01:24:11,896
We can be together and be happy.

1133
01:24:13,364 --> 01:24:16,060
Let me go with you to the judge.

1134
01:24:16,601 --> 01:24:19,434
And then we can start all over again.

1135
01:24:19,604 --> 01:24:22,129
Stop thinking about them.
Think about me.

1136
01:24:22,340 --> 01:24:24,535
I am thinking about you.

1137
01:24:24,709 --> 01:24:26,802
About what a swell guy you were...

1138
01:24:26,978 --> 01:24:30,038
...when you were alive.
- When I was alive?

1139
01:24:30,215 --> 01:24:33,048
If those people die, Joe Wilson dies.
You know that.

1140
01:24:33,218 --> 01:24:36,051
Wherever you go. Whatever you do.

1141
01:24:37,255 --> 01:24:39,587
I couldn't marry you now, Joe.

1142
01:24:39,891 --> 01:24:42,121
I couldn't marry a dead man.

1143
01:24:42,293 --> 01:24:45,490
All right, then, all right!
I don't need anybody!

1144
01:24:45,663 --> 01:24:47,130
Nobody!

1145
01:24:48,900 --> 01:24:51,164
Maybe this is crazy.

1146
01:24:52,504 --> 01:24:55,940
I can't help thinking we'd be
better off if you hadn't escaped.

1147
01:24:56,107 --> 01:24:58,598
That's what you can't help thinking?
Who cares?

1148
01:24:58,777 --> 01:25:01,268
This is a big night.
I ought to be celebrating.

1149
01:25:01,446 --> 01:25:04,438
And that's what I'm gonna do too!
Celebrate. Alone!

1150
01:25:04,616 --> 01:25:08,950
From now on, I'm gonna do everything
alone! I don't need any of you!

1151
01:25:22,133 --> 01:25:23,896
Hey.

1152
01:25:24,903 --> 01:25:26,268
- Yes?
- This stuff's weak.

1153
01:25:26,437 --> 01:25:28,132
- Get me bourbon.
- Sorry, sir...

1154
01:25:28,306 --> 01:25:31,969
...but with the kind of license
we have here, it's against the law.

1155
01:25:32,310 --> 01:25:33,800
All right. Give me a check.

1156
01:25:33,978 --> 01:25:38,210
- I'm sorry, sir, if you feel...
- No. It's all right. It's just, it's too noisy.

1157
01:25:38,416 --> 01:25:40,611
I don't like crowded places.

1158
01:26:02,807 --> 01:26:06,675
<i>Are you planning to do a lot of running</i>
<i>around in this room?</i>

1159
01:26:13,284 --> 01:26:14,911
Have a good time...

1160
01:26:15,920 --> 01:26:18,616
...and bye-bye.

1161
01:26:40,612 --> 01:26:42,705
Come in, mister.

1162
01:26:43,648 --> 01:26:45,809
- What's your pleasure?
- Double bourbon.

1163
01:26:45,984 --> 01:26:47,781
Yes, sir.

1164
01:26:57,829 --> 01:27:01,026
Midnight, and another day.

1165
01:27:06,204 --> 01:27:09,002
Two pages must've got hanged together.

1166
01:27:45,476 --> 01:27:48,445
<i>Do a good job of it!</i>
<i>What does it matter?</i>

1167
01:27:48,613 --> 01:27:52,014
<i>Twenty-two, 23, 25!</i>

1168
01:28:43,901 --> 01:28:46,529
Katherine! Katherine!

1169
01:29:05,223 --> 01:29:09,853
Katherine, don't leave me alone.

1170
01:29:21,773 --> 01:29:24,139
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury...

1171
01:29:24,308 --> 01:29:26,970
...have you agreed upon a verdict?

1172
01:29:27,178 --> 01:29:28,577
We have, Your Honor.

1173
01:29:28,746 --> 01:29:31,806
You will hand the verdict
to the bailiff.

1174
01:29:39,257 --> 01:29:43,159
We find in the case of the people of
the state versus the defendants...

1175
01:29:43,327 --> 01:29:47,423
...charged with the murder of Joseph
Wilson as set forth in the indictment.

1176
01:29:47,598 --> 01:29:49,725
Jasper Anderson, not guilty.

1177
01:29:50,835 --> 01:29:53,599
Gilbert Clark, not guilty.

1178
01:29:53,771 --> 01:29:57,639
Richard Durkin, guilty.

1179
01:29:57,809 --> 01:30:00,437
Walter Dubbs, guilty.

1180
01:30:00,611 --> 01:30:02,977
Kirby Dawson, guilty.

1181
01:30:03,147 --> 01:30:05,479
Frederick Garrett, guilty.

1182
01:30:05,650 --> 01:30:08,949
- Walter Gordon, guilty.
- No, no! I'm not. Not me!

1183
01:30:09,120 --> 01:30:11,418
Go ahead, go ahead, get it over with!

1184
01:30:30,041 --> 01:30:32,475
Order in the court!

1185
01:30:37,849 --> 01:30:40,181
Your Honor, I am Joseph Wilson.

1186
01:30:40,351 --> 01:30:42,615
Keep your seats!

1187
01:30:43,888 --> 01:30:46,118
- Go on.
- I know that by coming here...

1188
01:30:46,290 --> 01:30:49,316
...I saved the lives of these 22 people.

1189
01:30:49,527 --> 01:30:53,657
But that isn't why I'm here. I don't care
anything about saving them.

1190
01:30:53,865 --> 01:30:57,995
They're murderers. I know the law
says they're not because I'm still alive.

1191
01:30:58,169 --> 01:30:59,830
But that's not their fault.

1192
01:31:00,138 --> 01:31:04,472
And the law doesn't know that a lot of
things that were very important to me...

1193
01:31:04,642 --> 01:31:08,134
...silly things, maybe,
like a belief in justice...

1194
01:31:08,312 --> 01:31:11,406
...and an idea that men were civilized...

1195
01:31:12,049 --> 01:31:16,918
...and a feeling of pride that this country
of mine was different from all others.

1196
01:31:17,088 --> 01:31:21,286
The law doesn't know those things were
burned to death within me that night.

1197
01:31:21,859 --> 01:31:24,020
I came here today for my own sake.

1198
01:31:24,228 --> 01:31:26,093
I couldn't stand it anymore.

1199
01:31:26,297 --> 01:31:30,495
I couldn't stop thinking about them,
with every step and every breath I took.

1200
01:31:30,668 --> 01:31:33,899
And I didn't believe Katherine
when she said...

1201
01:31:36,007 --> 01:31:39,841
Katherine is the young lady
who was going to marry me.

1202
01:31:40,011 --> 01:31:43,344
Maybe someday after
I've paid for what I did...

1203
01:31:43,514 --> 01:31:46,381
...there'll be a chance to begin again.

1204
01:31:46,717 --> 01:31:49,049
And then maybe...

1205
01:31:49,420 --> 01:31:52,048
...Katherine and I...
- Joe.